---
layout: post
title: ASP.NET Core strongly typed Configuration in Startup class
published: true
---

Use configuration from appsettings.json in Startup.cs as POCO object.

appsettings.json

```
  "TrendSettings": {
    "Devices": [
      "10.10.96.124",
      "10.10.166.45"
    ],
    "ReadInterval": 500
  }
```

Settings.cs

```
public class Settings
{
    public int ReadInterval { get; set; }
    public IEnumerable<string> Devices { get; set; }
}
```

Startup.cs

```
public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services)
{
    services.AddMvc();
    
    settings = new TrendSettings();
    services.AddOptions();
    Configuration.GetSection(nameof(Settings)).Bind(settings);

    // here you can use settings
    services.AddSingleton<ITrend>(p => new UdcTrend(settings.ReadInterval));
}
